<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <%- include('partials/_head.ejs') %>
  <style>
    body {
      background-image: url("../css/b.jpg");
      background-size: cover;
      background-position: center;
      background-attachment: fixed;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      overflow: hidden;
    }

    .education-container {
      margin-top: 20px;
      padding: 20px;
      background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7);
      border-radius: 20px;
      color: white;
    }

    /* Change the color of the "Scan" text */
    .btn-primary {
      background-color: #ff6200; /* Orange color */
      border-color: #ff6200; /* Orange color */
    }

    .btn-primary:hover {
      background-color: #e05200; /* Darker shade of orange on hover */
      border-color: #e05200; /* Darker shade of orange on hover */
    }
  </style>
  <body>
    <%- include('partials/_header.ejs') %>
    <main role="main" class="container mt-4">
      <div class="row justify-content-between align-items-start">
        <div class="col-lg-6">
          <div class="card rounded education-container">
            <div class="card-body">
              <h1 class="card-title">Cybersecurity Education</h1>
              <p class="card-text">
                Below are some of the most common vulnerabilities explained in
                simple terms:
              </p>
              <!-- Add content explaining common vulnerabilities -->
              <ul class="text-light">
                <li>
                  <strong>Phishing:</strong> Phishing is like someone trying to
                  trick you into giving them your personal information, like
                  passwords or credit card numbers, by pretending to be someone
                  you trust, like a bank or a friend.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Malware:</strong> Malware is like a sneaky software
                  that can harm your computer or steal your information without
                  you knowing. It can come from downloading shady files or
                  clicking on suspicious links.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Weak Passwords:</strong> Weak passwords are like
                  leaving the front door of your house unlocked. If your
                  password is too easy to guess, hackers can easily break into
                  your accounts.
                </li>
                <!-- Add more vulnerabilities and explanations here -->
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
